entries.femaleVariant: Where's your friend?
You look awful.
What the hell happened? Look close to awful.
You see a man robbed of his implants, money and dignity. Look well.
It is not all bad. I am mostly unnoticed in the streets.
Friend you mentioned here?
Oda? He should be here any moment now.
And what's to stop her little errand boy from sellin' us out?
entries.maleVariant: And what's to stop her little errand boy from selling us out?

entries.femaleVariant: Yorinobu strangled his father.
Not gonna like what I have to say. Need a guarantee.
Looked like your typical family quarrel, until...
Was there. Saw what happened.
What Oda said... They return to Tokyo after the parade...
Do you not see? The parade...
We will need a precise map of Japantown.
We must do a proper reconnaissance first...
[Stand] Oda! Gonna help or not?
[Stand] Hanako should decide for herself.
Oda!
Oda. Not like we're asking for a whole lot, here.
We're talkin' about a guy who killed his father to seize control of Arasaka!
It is your turn to call on friends. Do you know a fixer who could help?
Fine friend, there. Got any more?
Alas, only him.
Takemura-san.
Oda.
Is this her? Your thief?
She is my witness. V.
Can speak for myself, you know.
So speak. I have been told you know things.
Just one brief meeting.
Hanako should decide if what we say is true. You can't decide for her.
Be very careful, my friend.
We are all so far from home.
[Stand] Well, we tried.
[Stand] Fine friends you got.
[Stand] Knew we'd crash.
Well... can't say we didn't try.
No way this was gonna work.
Hmm... yet, we walk away with a small measure of success...
We tried, yes, and obtained something useful...
Hm, how do you figure that?
[Stand] You're an Arasaka soldier! This is your duty.
Oda, you are an Arasaka soldier!
This is not a request. We remind you of your duty to be truthful to your superiors.
I did not come here to be lectured to by a thief.
Wasn't always what I am now. And your friend here didn't always look like a bum.
Feel free to join us. Plenty of room at the bottom of the heap.
Not enticed? Then do your duty. Tell Hanako what nobody else wants to hear.
That should be to him, as you say, food for thought.
Just gotta tell it like it is sometimes.
It is a shame nothing will come of it.
How come?
It should have been obvious. Oda is a perfectionist. He most fears to make a mistake.
If, somehow, we can get to Hanako-sama...
Hold on...
Er, hang on, not so fast!
Make it sound as easy as hacking a SCSM. But you said yourself – Hanako's got the tightest security in all Night City.
Correct. That is why I wish for you to contact us with the local fixer.
Yorinobu lunged at Saburo and started chokin' him…
entries.maleVariant: Yorinobu lunged at Saburo an' started chokin' him…

entries.femaleVariant: Not gonna like what I'm about to say. I need a guarantee I'm safe here...
Yorinobu strangled the old guy.
All right, then. Konpeki Plaza – I was there the night it happened.
What would you do now were you in my place?
I do no favors. I would deliver your head to Yorinobu-sama.
Consider yourself lucky that I am not you.
I will not.
But I will let you leave this place, this city, unharmed.
If I see either of you again, I will not be so lenient.
Seems pretty, uh, secluded here.
Silence. Not one word more.
The only thing I regret is that I came here to meet you.
You will bring death to your door.
But it is the truth! Hanako-sama must hear it!
My one concern is to keep her safe in this city forgotten by the gods.
Correct. Unlike you, I have not yet failed to keep my oath to do my duty.
I bring you this witness to his murder. And you dare to worry about a silly parade? Fool!
Can't ignore the truth!
But you can't ignore the truth!
There is a price on your head!
I do you a favor now by not cutting it off and taking it straight to Yorinobu-sama.
This gonna take much longer?
Sorry, but... this gonna take much longer?
It is appropriate for such a secret meeting.
You are. You have it.
V, you can trust Oda.
You will regret those words!
What?!
Gonna take an interest in this or not?
Will you help?
You cannot ignore this!
It is our chance, perhaps.
Willin' finally to give me the spec on 'im?
entries.maleVariant: Willing finally to give me the spec on 'im?

entries.femaleVariant: He is Hanako-sama's bodyguard.
Yes. And if he believes you, we will next meet with her.
He will not do that. He is a man of honor.
By car, huh? A good sign. He is usually camouflaged.
Hanako Arasaka's? From the carrier at anchor in the bay? Saburo's daughter?
Or he'll sell our asses out.
Sure you can trust him?
Sure you can trust him?
Hope he's not a stickler for Arasaka protocol.
Just hope he doesn't blindly follow Arasaka protocol.
Pff, right, 'cause Arasaka's ranks're chock-full of those.
entries.maleVariant: Right, 'cause Arasaka's ranks're chock-full of those.

entries.femaleVariant: Do not confuse true honor with the petty morals by which you live.
Yes.
Pff. Convincing, very.
I have nothing to lose. Is that better?
Worse. 'Cause I got plenty to lose!
What protocol?
Unwritten rules. Had 'em here in Night City. Could be different in Japan.
If IA got even a whiff of treason, they'd prep an enhanced interrogator and send two elite squads with air support to grab the suspect.
I understand the point you seek to make.
But if Oda has ulterior motives, he will need no elites, no air support, no one but himself. Trust me, I have seen him work.
Hm, that supposed to be reassuring?
entries.maleVariant: Hm. That supposed to be reassuring?

entries.femaleVariant: If it helps you stay calm, you can gaze at the sky.
Is she in danger?
Now? No. Yet during the parade to honor Arasaka-sama? Most certainly.
Know just the dame – Wakako Okada.
Slow down, this isn't gonna be easy.
Know just the fixer dame – Wakako Okada. Runs a pachinko parlor on Jig‑Jig Street.
We must pay this woman a visit.
I will meet you there. One other matter requires my attention.
It is good to see you, V.
Go on, V.
Bit your tongue?
What is the matter with you?
Probably for the best. We're takin' enough chances with this factory-refurbished ronin.
Good fuckin' riddance. One Arasaka whackjob is already plenty.
[Wait]
We must go to this street... Ji-- Ji? Argh, hard to say.
Ho! Why do you wander?! We have work to do!
You know fixer lady! I cannot go alone!
Ji-Ji Street... What is this name?
Just a Night City name.
Beware – you mock me… too often.
[Get in]
Well, we tried.
Knew we'd crash.
Fine friends you got.
